critique: This executive order primarily revises the language of a previous order (EO 12353) to update terminology related to the Combined Federal Campaign. It replaces terms like "voluntary agencies" with "voluntary health and welfare organizations" and makes minor adjustments to the administration of the campaign. There's no indication of a shift in ideological tilt, immigration approach, or a significant change in executive power, federalism, national security, economic regulation, or social inclusion. The changes appear to be administrative and clarifying in nature.
